Articles.Content: Thats really strange... I use IFS too, and have no problem changing the ore tanks to metal or rocket parts. I'm sure you've tried reinstalling IFS and this mod right? IFS updated recently.
I am using the IFS bundled with this mod. I'll try grabbing the update.
Huh, that seems to have fixed that.

Awesome, glad to hear you got it resolved!

Cheers.
Can I build single part?

On 07/06/2016 at 4:04 AM, Orange Nakor said:

Huh, that seems to have fixed that.

I'll update IFS then. You might have had a previous version installed separately. 

On 07/06/2016 at 11:58 AM, TheKurgan said:

Awesome, glad to hear you got it resolved!

Cheers.

Good initiative.

Can I build single part?

Anything!
I have not built single parts,  but I have filled storage containers with parts,  saved it as a ship,  and built that

Anything!

Uhm need to save it first as a ship or sub ?

Uhm need to save it first as a ship or sub ?

I see the workaround , but it would be nice to build single parts from a list

You need to save it as a ship that you could otherwise launch normally from the KSC launchpad.

As promised!

Colonizing Saturn - a Kerbal Epic

I had been looking at downloading the Extraplanetary Launch pads for a bit, and I was really reluctant, thanks to how huge it was, and how bad my computer is. But, just a few days ago, I heard of this mod (thanks to KottabosGames) and was instantly sold.  LOVE IT!  AWESOME IDEA! I can never thank you enough! I will be for sure mentioning this mod to my friends!

I can't seem to get this mod to work, or at least the construction port. Everything else (the Mobile Processing Lab, the Ore tanks, the Convert-o-tron) looks to be modified but the docking port jr, it still only has the decouple node and control from here in the right-click menu. By the way, using Linux, specifically Manjaro.

Here is my whole log:
